Taiaroa Head is a headland at the end of the Otago Peninsula in New Zealand, overlooking the mouth of the Otago Harbour.
The part of Taiaroa Head where Northern Royal Albatrosses breed is managed by the NZ Department of Conservation as a Nature Reserve with restricted entry.
Since they first successfully raised a chick at Taiaroa Head Royal albatross numbers have increased due to intensive management by Reserve Rangers.
